RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 28000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 121 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LET FREEDOM REIN trailed in the two path, tipped out and moved up in the five path under rousing around the far turn, took aim from the six path entering the lane, ran on to bid passing the eighth pole, floated in under right handed urging thru the final furlong and bumped with an inner foe twice while dueling with that foe to the wire, and got the winning bob. GIRLY THE BUTCHER broke out and brushed an outer rival, rated in the three path, was cued to range up and bid from the five path around the far turn, took over the lead and tipped back in to the three path entering the lane, kept on under left handed urging while meeting the challenge of an outer foe in the final furlong, bumped with that foe twice in the final sixteenth, and lost the bob to finish with place honors. RAMADHAAN (IRE) brushed with an inner foe leaving the gate, prompted the pace in the two path, briefly took the lead around the far turn, but was quickly overtaken by an outer foe, and evened out in the stretch for show. KIT CAN RUN tracked in the two path, was driven around the far turn and angled out to the five path in upper stretch, but flattened. KAREN'S REVENGE set the pace inside but yielded turning into the stretch. RIA FORMOSA stalked in the three path but gaveway around the far turn.
